        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 3:31PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lahontan Reservoir, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lahontan Reservoir, Fernley, Hazen, Silver Springs, Junction U.S 50
And NV 117 (sheckler Cutoff), and Us 50 At Lyon-Churchill Co Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
